# Raypx Project - Cursor AI Rules

## Tech Stack & Architecture
- Monorepo using Turborepo with pnpm workspace
- Frontend: Next.js 16 with React 19, TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components
- Linting/Formatting: Biome (not ESLint/Prettier)
- Package Manager: pnpm (required, do not use npm/yarn)

## Code Style Guidelines

### General
- Follow Biome configuration (biome.json)
- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- Max line width: 100 characters
- Use semicolons, double quotes for JavaScript/TypeScript
- Use `import type` for type imports
- Organize imports automatically (Biome handles this)
- Self-closing JSX elements when possible

### TypeScript
- Prefer explicit types over `any` (use `unknown` when type is truly unknown)
- Use `as const` assertions for literal types
- Avoid inferrable type annotations
- No parameter assignments
- Use default parameters last
- Use enum initializers
- Prefer single variable declarator

### React/Next.js
- Use functional components with hooks
- Follow Next.js 16 App Router patterns
- Use server components by default, client components only when needed
- Prefer composition over prop drilling
- Use clsx/cva for class names, they will be auto-sorted
- Avoid inline styles, use Tailwind classes

### File Structure
- Monorepo: `apps/` for applications, `packages/` for shared code
- Feature-based organization in apps
- Shared UI components in `packages/ui/`
- Use absolute imports with `@/` prefix

### Commands
- Install dependencies: `pnpm install`
- Run dev server: `pnpm dev` (specific app: `pnpm dev:app`, `pnpm dev:web`)
- Build: `pnpm build`
- Lint: `pnpm lint` (uses Biome)
- Format: `pnpm format` (uses Biome)

## AI Instructions
- When generating new components, check existing shadcn/ui components first
- Follow the existing code patterns in the codebase
- Always run `pnpm lint` and `pnpm format` before considering code complete
- Use Biome for all linting and formatting, never add ESLint/Prettier
- Respect the monorepo structure - place code in the correct app/package
- For UI changes, ensure Tailwind classes are used (no inline styles)
- Always check if similar functionality exists before creating new code
